<br>
The basic premise takes place just after the fourth season. The crew of Moya will not be involved... for the most part. Each participant will be making their own new character and it is based on the scenario. <br>
<br>
The scenario is as thus - just after the destruction of the crystherium plants on Katrazi, the Scarrans are desperate to secure a new source of the plants. The plants do not grow on many worlds - but one of the species who do know about the plants are the Delvians (because they are in fact sentient plants). The problem is that the Delvians are under peacekeeper protection, but only on the border of Peacekeeper space. A group of Scarrans will lead a diplomatic meeting to the Delvian planet, to begin negotiations to secure a crystherium mother plant. Scorpius will of course, not allow this. But he's too far away, so he has a squad of peacekeepers who are ordered to not let the Scarrans have the crystherium by any means possible. (Destruction isn't an option because of the delvians affinity to plants)<br>
<br>
Also, Scarran and Peacekeeper relations are really really *really* frayed at this point. It's quite likely that the interference in the negotiations will cause a war between the two species - a war that the Peacekeepers are not in a good position to fight at all. (Further incentive for the Delvians to aid the Scarrans?) <br>
<br>
So there's three basic groups in the scenario, so I think it will be a lot of fun to play out and might make a good starting point for future. <br>
<br>
